    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:h /magic`\n\nHi,\nIt can be tedious to escape regex operators in searches when working frequently with search and substitute.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIs it possible to create some config option like `vim.g.verymagic = true` which makes all search patterns automatically use verymagic? This would alleviate us from having to chose between either writing `\\v` at the start of each of our searches or having to escape all sorts of regex operators.",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-31T21:39:31Z",
