        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That would be confusing, no? \n\n> But perhaps it's possible to have an option that only affects manually entered :substutute and /search?\n\nFrom `:h :substitute`:\n\n> Note that there is no flag to change the \"magicness\" of the pattern.  A\ndifferent command is used instead, or you can use |/\\v| and friends.  The\nreason is that the flags can only be found by skipping the pattern, and in\norder to skip the pattern the \"magicness\" must be known.  Catch 22!\n",
            "created_at": "2026-03-31T21:30:13Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38652#issuecomment-4165711357",
